#using docker machine and compose
1. Create docker machine on cloud
# set up VM with public IP
 






2. Run nginx service as docker container
#Run nginx on port 80 as container mapped to port 80 to host







3. Create domain name and configure
# create domain name and point to public IP of VM






4. Run registry service as docker container
# Run registry service as container on same host (port 5000)








5. Run proxy nginx to registry


6. Configure SSL with trusted cert
# Configure SSL on nginx (i.e nginx listening on port 443) . SSL is using a cert from a trusted auhhority

7. Enable basic auth - only authorised user can access registry





8. Manage repositories using docker


